    "code": "40A",
    "name": "Levels of Emergence & Scale Transitions",
    "description": "Emergence occurs when simple local interactions create complex global patterns that couldn't be predicted from examining the components alone‚Äîmany molecules moving in particular ways eventually produce war memorials and economic policy. Different phenomena matter at different scales, with cells forming humans, humans forming communities, and interactions between levels affecting all other levels. Moving toward depth over breadth reveals how simple rules at one level create sophisticated behavior at higher levels.",
