      "Simple frameworks produce more reliable analysis than complex ones. Charlie Munger demonstrates that simplicity, thrift, duty, and hard work‚Äîstraightforward principles‚Äîgenerate elegant outcomes more dependably than sophisticated financial models. The waterwheel example shows systems creating double-spiral patterns from simple physics, never settling yet maintaining bounded behavior that reveals order through chaos."
